<subSubSection id="C36165495E31FF919E85FDE9FE9D9B37" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436C25E31FF919E85FDE9FE9D9B37" blockId="8.[166,1225,630,785]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
The subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919FD7FDE9FDED9AB7" box="[393,543,630,657]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chrysopinae">Chrysopinae</taxonomicName>
includes the largest number of species, which occur in all continents (excluding 
<collectingCountry id="F36C76525E31FF919FF1FD09FDC29A97" box="[431,560,662,689]" name="Antarctica" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
). About 65 species of 12 genera are known from Europe (Canard, 2004), including 23 species of eight genera (
<emphasis id="B90FEAD05E31FF919D77FD29FC099AD6" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919D77FD29FC5E9AF6" box="[809,940,694,720]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Italochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Italochrysa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919DE7FD29FBDB9AF6" authorityName="Leach &amp; Brewster" authorityYear="1815" box="[953,1065,694,720]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysopa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919A68FD29FB369AF6" authorityName="Steinmann" authorityYear="1964" box="[1078,1220,694,720]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysoperla</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919EF8FD49FEB29AD6" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1911" box="[166,320,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysotropia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysotropia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919F07FD49FE089AD6" authorityName="Holzel" authorityYear="1970" box="[345,506,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Cunctochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cunctochrysa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919C4CFD48FD969AD6" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[530,612,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Nineta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nineta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919C23FD49FCC29AD6" authorityName="Lacroix" authorityYear="1920" box="[637,816,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Peyerimhoffina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peyerimhoffina</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919D17FD49FC099AD6" authorityName="Tsukaguchi" authorityYear="1995" box="[841,1019,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Pseudomallada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudomallada</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="F36C76525E31FF919A36FD49FB3A9AD7" box="[1128,1224,726,753]" name="Ukraine" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B335E31FF919EF0FD69FE909B37" author="Serediuk, G. V." box="[174,354,758,785]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="141 - 148" refId="ref6636" refString="Serediuk, G. V. 2015. Green lacewings (Insecta: Neuroptera. Chrysopidae) fauna of Ukraine. Proceeding of the State Natural History Museum, 31, 141 - 148. URL: http: // nbuv. gov. ua / UJRN / Nzdpm _ 2015 _ 31 _ 18 [In Ukrainian]." type="journal article" year="2015">Serediuk, 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
